tudents must make crucial or dramatic decisions, though these decisions need not align with the historical record. In doing so, they learn, through action and strategic consideration, the impact of real individuals and groups of people on the course of history.There is a quiet revolution underway in how history is taught to undergraduates. Can You Beat Churchill? hopes to make it a noisy one.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHistoryxStudy and teachingxSimulation methods. 0aSimulation games in education. 4aDiplomatic History. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aHistory. 7aEDUCATION / Experimental Methods.2bisacsh  asimulation design, Simulations in the classroom, classroom simulation, student engagement, participatory history,.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2021 Englishz978311075406308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2021z9783110753950oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150175566840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501755668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501755668/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075406-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-a